  {
    "hotel_id": "69568",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/sparks-life-jakarta/hotel/jakarta-id.html",
    "name": "Sparks Life Jakarta, ARTOTEL Curated",
    "detail": "The SPARKS hotel is a pretty well known landmark the Jakarta. The Hotel itself could serve as a destination resort for a single Male travler with it's 1. Karaoke bar, 2. MnB Lounge (Tuesday and Thursday is Ladies night - free vodka between 9 and 11 I think) and 3. The Spa which has very nicely appointed rooms with glass and granite showers. However, It is not within walking distance of anything other than Lokasari Plaza. However, with it's Blue Bird Taxi service, you can get to most parts of Jakarta within 30 minutes for a pretty cheap price which makes it pretty convenient. The rooms are on the small side, but pretty. The beds are wide and firm. The stand up shower is great and the water is HOT ( a good thing). The tile floors can get quite slippery when wet and to their credit this Hotel provides non skid slippers in every room. If you are traveling with a family you may want them to remove the multicolored condoms and lubricants from the nightstand. ( they were placed in every room I observed) The items in the mini bar run about 4 times what they would sell for outside. If you have guests they are likely to begin to immediately help themselves - sharing of food is very common in Indonesia.",
